[
    {
        "content": "<p>So I did some research on how JavaScript handles default values, and wanted to document that here.  Do we even need <code>?</code> in the type definition?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">--Do default values need to apply to record type only?</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">optionalRecord</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">optionalRecord</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">--JavaScript allows default values for function arguments with equal sign regardless of the type</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">primitveType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">n</span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">n</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span>\n<span class=\"kt\">ObjectType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">--Can default values be applied to all types in ROC?  Should ROC even default values?</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">primitiveType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">primitiveType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">c</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callPrimitiveType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">primitiveType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--I used an underscore place holder to indicate the absence of a value</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callTupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--What to put in the middle here to represent an explicit missing value?</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callRecordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">c</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--Easier since we can just not pass b.</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"c1\">--More complex scenario with renaming variables for multiple instances of the same type</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">--Renaming variables and defaulting those variables would have to be supported at the same time.</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">--Destructuring inside the function definition</span>\n<span class=\"kt\">MyTuple</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyTuple</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyTuple</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">),(</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">-</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callTupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kt\">MyRecord</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyRecord</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyRecord</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">},{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">-</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callRecordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">--Destructuring in the body of the function</span>\n<span class=\"kt\">MyTuple</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyTuple</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyTuple</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">tuple1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">tuple2</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">tuple1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">tuple2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">-</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callTupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nv\">tupleType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kt\">MyRecord</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyRecord</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">MyRecord</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">obj1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">obj2</span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">obj1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"err\">?</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">obj2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">a2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">-</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b1</span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"nv\">b2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nv\">callRecordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"nv\">recordType</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The difficulty is ROC would have to know that the properties or values eventually get a default value inside the body or function definition if they are not provided when calling the function.  If you don't pass a required value to the function, and there is no default, then ROC would obviously need to throw a compiler error.</p>",
        "id": 423233416,
        "sender_full_name": "Brian Teague",
        "timestamp": 1708837999
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes, that's what the <code>?</code> in the type solves <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 423233979,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708838640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(it conveys that the field can safely be omitted because a default has been provided, and if it turns out that's not true, then the compiler can tell you about the disagreement)</p>",
        "id": 423234060,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708838720
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would it be beneficial to ROC to add<code>?</code> for any type including tuples, not just records only?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">defaultNum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span>\n<span class=\"n\">defaultNum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">\\</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">callDefaultNum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">defaultNum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 423234359,
        "sender_full_name": "Brian Teague",
        "timestamp": 1708839079
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it would be detrimental. <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 423234723,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708839546
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>my conclusion from looking into optional positional arguments and \"nullable types\" in other languages is that they would lead to worse APIs in Roc, and so we should explicitly choose not to support either</p>",
        "id": 423234804,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708839628
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in contrast, I do think optional labeled arguments are valuable</p>",
        "id": 423234818,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708839659
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and that was the original motivation for optional record fields</p>",
        "id": 423234835,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708839678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's worth exploring alternative designs to the current optional record field system, but I don't think introducing nullable types or optional positional arguments are things Roc should have <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 423234898,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708839754
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/Default.20values.20in.20ROC.20compared.20to.20JavaScript/near/423234804\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>my conclusion from looking into optional positional arguments and \"nullable types\" in other languages is that they would lead to worse APIs in Roc, and so we should explicitly choose not to support either</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Can you explain this more? Specifically optional positional arguments. Not sure why nullable types matter for this. I am just thinking about default values.</p>",
        "id": 423236933,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1708842141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>basically I looked at:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>other languages which have this feature, and how it's used in their ecosystems, and then asked \"how would I write this in a world where this feature wasn't available?\" followed by \"ok and now which world seems better?\"</li>\n<li>if I wanted to use it in current Roc functions (e.g. a <code>Str.join</code> that takes an optional <code>Str</code> for what to intersperse between the strings, defaulting to <code>\"\"</code>), where would it make sense to use it? And then same question: does it seem like the resulting world of Roc APIs is better or worse?</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 423237347,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708842644
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and it seemed like in both situations the \"positional optional arguments get used\" designs were worse</p>",
        "id": 423237368,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708842673
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>leading me to conclude that those other languages (without naming names) would have better APIs if the languages dropped support for that feature <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 423237443,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708842734
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's an interesting exercise - like try it for some Roc APIs, see where it feels like it would make sense to use that feature if it existed, and then compare it to the alternative design where that feature doesn't exist (both times trying to aim for the nicest design possible, with the only variable changing being whether or not you're using optional positional arguments in some way)</p>",
        "id": 423237545,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708842846
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And this comment is specific to positional optional args? Not named optional args?</p>",
        "id": 423238019,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1708843444
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah</p>",
        "id": 423257183,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1708861152
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree with that outcome regarding default value handling <span aria-label=\"wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f609\" role=\"img\" title=\"wink\">:wink:</span> but methodology-wise, aren't there situations in which you need to change more than one variable?</p>\n<p>Limiting it to a single variable change at a time limits the range of outcomes that can be explored, since language features (and omissions) work together. Changing just one variable from X=A -&gt; X=B might be a worse world (as might any change to X alone), yet X=B Y=D might be an altogether better world than the current arrangement of X=A Y=C</p>\n<p>I'm just zooming in on your use of the words \"with the only variable changing\"...</p>",
        "id": 424411673,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1709386370
    }
